# Day 5
what I learned:
- The networking fundamentals
- Difference between Private and Public IP addresses and under what criteria they could change
- DNS works in browsers, as well the advantages and the disadvantages of DNS cache
- TCP focuses on accuracy over speed and UDP focuses on vice versa
- TCP ensures accuracy with: three-way handshake, packet tracking number and assembled properly after being sent
- UDP ensures speed with: no handshake, no re-sent lost packets
- ports ensure that data do not get mixed up when a device is handling multiple activities over same router connection
- port 80: less secure (HTTP, no padlock) 
- port 443: more secure for banking and shopping (HTTPS, has padlock)
- port 25 & 587: specifically for sending emails
